title: Presidental Nominations Sent To The Senate, 4/21/2009 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




April 21, 2009

 



Presidental Nominations Sent To The Senate, 4/21/2009




THE WHITE HOUSE Office of the Press Secretary _____________________________________________________________ FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                       April 21, 2009    NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE: Jonathan Steven Adelstein, of South Dakota, to be Administrator, Rural Utilities Service, Department of Agriculture, vice James M. Andrew, resigned. Thomasina Rogers, of Maryland, to be a Member of the Occupational Safety and Health Review Commission for a term expiring April 27, 2015. (Reappointment) ##
